  "grammar": {
  "en": {
    "title": "Grammar Spot",
    "content": "<strong>I'm = I am</strong><br>name's = name is<br>What's = What is<br><br><strong>am/are/is</strong><br>I <u>am</u> Sandra.<br>How <u>are</u> you?<br>This <u>is</u> John.<br><br><strong>my/your</strong><br><u>My</u> name's Hiro.<br>What's <u>your</u> name?<br><br><strong>Plurals</strong><br>one book → two <u>books</u><br>one sandwich → ten <u>sandwiches</u>"
  },
  "ja": {
    "title": "文法ポイント",
    "content": "<strong>I'm = I am</strong><br>（私は〜です）<br><strong>name's = name is</strong><br>（名前は〜です）<br><strong>What's = What is</strong><br>（〜は何ですか？）<br><br><strong>am/are/is（be動詞）</strong><br>I <u>am</u> Sandra.（私はサンドラです）<br>How <u>are</u> you?（お元気ですか？）<br>This <u>is</u> John.（こちらはジョンです）<br><br><strong>my/your（所有格）</strong><br><u>My</u> name's Hiro.（私の名前はヒロです）<br>What's <u>your</u> name?（あなたの名前は何ですか？）<br><br><strong>複数形</strong><br>one book → two <u>books</u>（本）<br>one sandwich → ten <u>sandwiches</u>（サンドイッチ）<br>※英語では名詞に -s/-es を付けて複数形を作ります。"
  },
  "fr": {
    "title": "Grammaire",
    "content": "<strong>I'm = I am</strong><br>（Je suis）<br><strong>name's = name is</strong><br>（s'appelle / le nom est）<br><strong>What's = What is</strong><br>（Qu'est-ce que c'est ? / Quel est... ?）<br><br><strong>am/are/is（verbe être）</strong><br>Je <u>suis</u> Sandra.<br>Comment <u>allez</u>-vous ?<br>C'<u>est</u> John.<br><br><strong>my/your（possessifs）</strong><br><u>Mon</u> nom est Hiro.<br>Quel est <u>ton</u> nom ?<br><br><strong>Pluriels</strong><br>one book → two <u>books</u>（un livre → deux livres）<br>one sandwich → ten <u>sandwiches</u>（un sandwich → dix sandwiches）<br>※En français, on ajoute -s ou -x pour former le pluriel des noms."
  },
  "ko": {
    "title": "문법 포인트",
    "content": "<strong>I'm = I am</strong><br>（나는 ~입니다 / 저는 ~입니다）<br><strong>name's = name is</strong><br>（이름은 ~입니다）<br><strong>What's = What is</strong><br>（~은/는 무엇입니까?）<br><br><strong>am/are/is（be동사）</strong><br>I <u>am</u> Sandra.（저는 샌드라입니다）<br>How <u>are</u> you?（어떻게 지내세요?）<br>This <u>is</u> John.（이분은 존입니다）<br><br><strong>my/your（소유격）</strong><br><u>My</u> name's Hiro.（제 이름은 히로입니다）<br>What's <u>your</u> name?（당신의 이름은 무엇입니까?）<br><br><strong>복수형</strong><br>one book → two <u>books</u>（책 한 권 → 책 두 권）<br>one sandwich → ten <u>sandwiches</u>（샌드위치 하나 → 샌드위치 열 개）<br>※영어에서는 명사에 -s/-es를 붙여 복수형을 만듭니다."
  }
  },
